COMPONENT NAME: IKM MSSQL Incremental Update COMPONENT VERSION: 10.1.3.2 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 10.1.3 and above
Description : - Integration Knowledge Module - Integrates data in an Microsoft SQL Server target table in incremental update mode. - Inexistent rows are inserted; already existing rows are updated. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled. - When using this module with a journalized source table, it is possible to synchronize deletions.
Restrictions: - Comparison of data is made using the Update Key defined in the interface. It has to be set. - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore. - Deletes are commited regardless of the COMMIT option
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Identifies and updates rows of the Target Datastore depending on the value of the UPDATE_KEY columns of the target datastore records.
Commit all data inserted or updated in the target datastore.
Check this option to synchronize journalized deletions. This option will take effect only if one source table is journalized in your interface.
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected from a previous control.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
create table <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]\t[DEST_WRI_DT] NULL", ",\n\t", "", "INS or UPD")%>, IND_UPDATE char(1) )

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",","[COL_NAME]", ",
	" , "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> ) select <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",","[EXPRESSION]", ",
	" , "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> where IND_UPDATE = 'I'

update T set <%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]	= S.[COL_NAME]", ",
	" , "", "(((UPD and !TRG) and !UK) and REW)")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",","T.[COL_NAME]	= [EXPRESSION]", ",
	" , "", "(((UPD and TRG) and !UK) and REW)")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S, <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]	= S.[COL_NAME]", "
and	", "", "UK") %> and S.IND_UPDATE = 'U'

update S set IND_UPDATE = 'N' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S, <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]\t= S.[COL_NAME]", "\n\tand\t", "", "UK")%> <%=snpRef.getColList("and\t","((T.[COL_NAME] = S.[COL_NAME]) or (T.[COL_NAME] IS NULL and S.[COL_NAME] IS NULL))", "\nand\t", "", "((UPD and !TRG) and !UK)")%>

update S set IND_UPDATE = 'U' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S, <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]\t= S.[COL_NAME]", "\nand\t", "", "UK")%>

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS or UPD) and !TRG)")%>, IND_UPDATE ) select <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS or UPD) and !TRG)")%>, 'I' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> E where not exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= E.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "UK")%> ) and E.ORIGIN = '<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ERR_TYPE = '<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>'

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%>, IND_UPDATE ) select <%=snpRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ",\n\t", "", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%>, <% if (snpRef.getPop("HAS_JRN").equals("0")) { %> 'I' IND_UPDATE <%} else {%> JRN_FLAG <%}%> from <%=snpRef.getFrom()%> where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJoin()%> <%=snpRef.getFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=snpRef.getHaving()%>

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

delete from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> where exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> I where <%=snpRef.getColList("", snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A") + ".[COL_NAME]\t= I.[COL_NAME]", "\n\t\tand\t", "", "UK")%> and IND_UPDATE = 'D' )
Remove deleted rows from flow table
